    ],
    "claim": "Borrow validation and account-health accounting trust oracle prices blindly; if a reserve price becomes 0, `amountInETH` becomes 0, the new borrow needs no collateral, and the resulting debt also contributes 0 to health-factor calculations.",
    "impact": "Any user with any positive collateral can repeatedly borrow the entire liquidity of a zero-priced reserve without becoming liquidatable, creating immediate full-reserve insolvency.",
    "paths": [
      "Oracle returns 0 for a borrowable asset -> `LendingPool._executeBorrow()` computes `amountInETH == 0` -> `ValidationLogic.validateBorrow()` accepts the borrow -> `GenericLogic.calculateUserAccountData()` continues to count that debt as 0 -> attacker drains the reserve."
    ]
  },
